equation_narrative.headline: Proline emerges late from polar-dominated context via specialized MLP prediction channels
equation_narrative.story: Through layers 1-23, the model assembles a representation dominated by polar residues (S, T) and small hydrophobics (A), consistent with the local sequence context (TLEVE_SDTIE) and 6 structural contacts. The logit lens shows serine leading at 22.6% initially, with threonine peaking at 38.4% by L23, but these reflect the polar character of the gathered context, not predictions. The transition begins at L24 when attention shifts away from polar features. Proline-specific MLP neurons activate decisively at L29-32, with N31:5095 contributing 1.43 projection and N30:4229 adding 0.69, driving proline from 2.9% at L23 to 65.2% at L33.

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 gather predominantly local sequence information with limited structural input. Six structural contacts provide modest context, while only 2 co-evolving positions suggest weak evolutionary constraints. Early features (F1:5480, F1:9146, F1:1508 at 45+ projection) encode positional and sequence identity. By L9, features like F9:5728 (60.0 proj) and F9:1281 (55.1 proj) continue building local context representation. The logit lens trajectory through L23 shows polar residues (S peaking at 40.6% at L27, T at 38.4% at L23) dominating, reflecting the polar-rich local environment rather than model predictions. Mid-layer features at L18 (F18:244, F18:7777) show lower projections (8-9), indicating a shift from identity encoding to more abstract contextual features.
perception_phase.context_character: The assembled context is polar-dominated with small hydrophobic character, consistent with the TLEVE_SDTIE sequence environment. The position appears surface-exposed or in a flexible region given the prevalence of small, polar residues in the local context and weak structural coupling.
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 6 residues within contact distance, providing modest 3D context
Co-evolutionary signal: 2 coupled positions, indicating weak functional constraints
Local sequence: Strong polar signal from flanking S, T, E, D residues drives early representation character
L1 attention features: F1:5480, F1:9146, F1:1508 (42-45 proj) encode positional identity
L9 context assembly: F9:5728 (60.0 proj), F9:1281 (55.1 proj) build sequence context representation

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes between L27-32. At L24, attention actively erases polar signal (−2.9 delta from attention). Proline-specific MLP neurons activate at L29 (N29:3462 with 0.58 proj, N29:2487 with 0.48 proj) and surge at L30-31 (N30:4229 at 0.69 proj, N31:5095 at 1.43 proj). Layer 32 delivers the decisive shift with 11.6 MLP delta, driven by specialized proline-voting neurons. Final attention features at L33 (F33:9048, F33:6423 at 85+ proj) consolidate the proline prediction.
decision_phase.transition: At L23-24, the model shifts from context assembly to prediction. L23 shows threonine at 38.4% in the logit lens, reflecting accumulated polar context. L24 attention erases 2.9 logit via polar-suppressing heads, while MLP contributes −0.36. This marks the boundary where representation character (polar-leaning) gives way to amino-acid-specific prediction channels that recognize proline as the structural solution despite the polar environment.

candidates.narrative: Proline remains nearly invisible through perception (1.6% at L17, 2.9% at L23), then surges in the decision phase. The breakthrough occurs at L29 where N29:3462 (0.58 proj) and N29:2487 (0.48 proj) activate, followed by massive MLP support at L30-31: N30:4229 (0.69 proj), N31:5095 (1.43 proj). Layer 32 delivers 11.6 MLP delta, the largest velocity event, with specialized proline neurons overriding the polar context. Proline rises from 12.3% at L29 to 65.2% at L33.
key_evidence: N31:5095 (1.43 proj) — strongest proline-specific neuron, votes P > A > C
N30:4229 (0.69 proj) — proline writer with P > D > L preference
L32 MLP: 11.6 delta toward answer, largest velocity event
F33:9048 (86.2 proj) — final attention feature consolidating proline

candidates.narrative: Serine leads the logit lens at initialization (22.6% at L0) and peaks at 40.6% at L27, reflecting the polar character of the assembled representation. The model reads flanking serine at position 21 and the polar-rich local environment (E, D, T neighbors). This is not a prediction but rather the representation's chemical signature. Serine declines sharply after L27 as proline-specific prediction channels activate, falling to 13.7% by L33.
key_evidence: L0-L27: Logit lens reflects polar context character, not prediction
Peaks at 40.6% at L27 before decision phase
N27:35 (−0.61 proj) erases polar signal, votes N/H/R over S

candidates.narrative: Threonine peaks at 38.4% at L23, the highest logit-lens value in the perception phase, reflecting the strong polar context and the presence of threonine at position 16. At L24, attention actively suppresses threonine (−2.9 delta), marking the perception-to-decision transition. Threonine briefly leads again at L22-24 but collapses to 1.2% by L33 as proline neurons dominate. The early prominence was representation character, not a genuine prediction.
key_evidence: L23: 38.4% peak reflects polar context assembly
L24 attention: −2.9 delta erases threonine signal
N23:2173 (−0.46 proj) votes N/T/R, suppressing proline

candidates.narrative: Alanine shows 20.0% at L0, reflecting small hydrophobic character in the embedding, then declines through perception to 4.4% at L23. It resurges slightly in the decision phase (12.8% at L33) as some MLP neurons vote for small residues. N14:3458 (−0.37 proj) strongly votes A > M > F, suppressing proline. Alanine remains a secondary candidate throughout, never mounting a serious challenge to proline's late dominance.
key_evidence: L0: 20.0% from small hydrophobic embedding character
N14:3458 (−0.37 proj) votes A > M > F, anti-proline
Final 12.8% reflects small-residue preference in some neurons

turning_points.description: The perception-to-decision transition occurs here. L21-23 show the representation reaching peak polar character (S at 24.9% L21, T at 38.4% L23), with features encoding the assembled context. At L24, attention delivers −2.9 delta (largest attention eraser in the network), actively suppressing the polar signal. F24:5080 (29.5 proj) and other L24 attention features shift the representation away from polar character. This marks where context assembly ends and amino-acid-specific prediction begins.

Proline's decisive emergence. L29 activates initial proline neurons (N29:3462 at 0.58 proj, N29:2487 at 0.48 proj), lifting proline from 2.9% to 12.3%. L30-31 bring massive MLP support: N30:4229 (0.69 proj), N31:5095 (1.43 proj, the strongest single neuron). L32 delivers the knockout blow with 11.6 MLP delta, the largest velocity event in the network, driven by specialized proline-voting neurons overriding all polar context. Proline jumps from 12.3% at L29 to 65.2% at L33.

deep_dives.label: Early context features L1-9
deep_dives.caption: L1 features (F1:5480, F1:9146, F1:1508) encode positional identity and sequence context. L9 features (F9:5728 at 60.0 proj, F9:1281 at 55.1 proj) show continued context assembly. These high projections reflect the representation's polar character from local sequence, not predictions.

deep_dives.label: Mid-layer representation L18
deep_dives.caption: L18 features show lower projections (F18:244 at 9.5, F18:7777 at 8.9), indicating a shift from identity encoding to more abstract contextual features. The representation is transitioning from 'what's here' to 'what should go here'.

deep_dives.label: Decision transition L24
deep_dives.caption: L24 marks the perception-to-decision boundary. F24:5080 (29.5 proj) leads attention features that actively suppress polar signal (−2.9 attention delta). This is where amino-acid-specific prediction channels first activate.

deep_dives.label: Proline MLP surge L29-31
deep_dives.caption: The decisive proline prediction emerges here. L29: N29:3462 (0.58 proj), N29:2487 (0.48 proj). L30: N30:4229 (0.69 proj). L31: N31:5095 (1.43 proj, strongest neuron). These specialized neurons vote specifically for proline, overriding the polar context assembled in perception.

deep_dives.label: L32 MLP knockout
deep_dives.caption: L32 delivers 11.6 MLP delta, the largest velocity event in the network. N32:4345 (0.55 proj) votes T/P/H, N32:782 (0.48 proj) votes P/M/A. This layer consolidates proline's dominance, lifting it from 35% to final 65%.

deep_dives.label: Final consolidation L33
deep_dives.caption: L33 attention features (F33:9048 at 86.2 proj, F33:6423 at 85.6 proj) consolidate the proline prediction. These high-projection features represent the model's final committed state, integrating all evidence for proline.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts proline despite assembling a strongly polar-dominated context through L23. The key insight is the separation of perception and decision: layers 1-23 faithfully encode the polar local environment (S, T, E, D neighbors), reflected in the logit lens showing serine and threonine prominence. But this is context character, not prediction. The decision phase (L24-33) activates specialized proline-voting MLP neurons that recognize proline as the structural solution—likely for its unique backbone constraint and turn-inducing properties—independent of the polar chemistry. The strongest evidence is the L32 MLP surge (11.6 delta) driven by neurons like N31:5095 (1.43 proj) that vote specifically for proline, overriding all accumulated polar signal.
